Name: Canezahpo
Comments:
Dark Places trailer

Libby Day is a fragile and unemployed woman struggling to get away from the demons of her past. as a child of just 7, She bore witness to the violent murder of her mother and two sisters and even stood up in court to asiame scam accuse her older brother Ben of the crimes. citizens were happy to take her word for it when it was unearthed that he was involved in Satanic activity, But now more than 20 years on the entire trauma is finally back for a visit with consequences no one could've foreseen. Broke after living off charity funds all her life, She readily accepts a cash payment to make a look and feel at a meeting of the Kill Club; A group specialising in murder mysteries and who have a particular interest in the case of her family namely as they do not believe her brother was the killer. While sceptical of their reminiscences, She soon agrees to help them pick apart what happened, Re visiting her memories of that fateful night and even seeing her brother somebody in charge of since his trial.

This haunting thriller based on the novel of the same name by Gillian Flynn ('Gone Girl') Has been written and directed by the award winning Gilles Paquet Brenner ('Sarah's Key', 'Walled In'). It explores the unreliability of eye witness testimony and how what we see may not always be our opinion. 'Dark Places' hit theatres in August 2015.
